FuncDef: The display license revoke-ticket chassis command displays the invalidation code of an invalid license file.

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies the ID of a chassis.
-

ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
To view the invalidation code of an invalid license file, run the display license revoke-ticket chassis command. The GTL invalidation code indicates that the license key is invalid and that a new GTL file can be applied for.
Prerequisites
An invalid license file exists in the current device. Otherwise, no entry is displayed in the display license revoke-ticket command output.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
